<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO COOK</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct 25 16:47:14 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John and Tom, thanks for your support.  Glad to see you back Tom.<br><br>
Let me apologize up front on the length of this message but I don't know how to cover what I want to say without just saying it.<br><br>
Cook,  I know I haven't been denied the right to post.  But I don't want to post only to have potshots directed at everything I say.  You mentioned that when you first came online others challenged you at first for verification.  This is not the first time I have been on-line in this forum.  I posted under the name of Betty a long time ago.  What do I do to verify who I am and stop the challenges. Let me know when you figure out what is sticking in the back of your mind that concerns you about me. I asked John....what do they want?  I ask you the same.  <br><br>
If we can get past the question of &quot;Is this a woman who served in Vietnam&quot; assuming that is even the real issue, then I don't have any problems about logically examining what I have said or explaining why I have a particular opinion. I do have problems with a broad stroked jabs such as whether I know anything about how the military handled prosthesis for amputees.  The equivalent is me telling a grunt who served in Nam that he doesn't know anything about claymore mines or killing zones.  I don't want to get into a yelling match of  Do So, Do Not, Do So. Do Not.<br><br>
I respect honesty.  I don't require anyone to beat around the bush.  I try to be honest.  Sometimes the memory isn't what it used to be and I mess up because I don't remember perfectly but you can be certain I am telling you and anyone else on this site the truth as I know it.<br><br>
Art raised an issue, I didn't answer directly because I thought he was explaining his position and it wasn't a question.  But this whole  ball of wax surrounding the name Class Lass versus Classless keeps coming up.  So, I go on the record.  I am not now, nor ever have I been a communist, or a Kali Tal fan or student.  I am an American who believes in Democracy. I would never have been permitted to accompany the troops in the field if there was even a hint that I was a communist or a communist sympathizer anywhere in my  background.  We had access to  troop strength and location information and freedom to move in country.  There was no way the  military would have allowed us to be there if our allegiance was in any way shape or form questionable.  I am classless in regards to judging others along class, racial or sexual lines.  My family was pretty poor and I didn't think that made me any less of a person.  I didn't and still don't think people should be judged based upon the family they were born into.  What matters is what you make of yourself.  I  worked my way through college and I am not going to apologize for the fact that I graduated, nor do I look down on others who didn't choose to take that path. I believe that everyone has something about them that makes them special.   I was considered an officer by the military.  But whether a man was an officer or not was irrelevant to me personally.  I wanted to know what they were like as a person.<br><br>
I am not from Tennessee or even visited there yet.  Seems like there are some great people from Tennessee though and I am missing alot from never having been there.   I am not politically active outside of the fact that I vote in every election.  You may find me politically correct, but when that happens it isn't because I was told to act a certain way its because what is considered politically correct has caught up with the way I believe.  I have had a lot of varied experiences such as working with an inner city mission with poor whites, conducting vacation bible schools in Harlem, going to an embassy dinner,  and living in other countries.  Those experiences have showed me that the way I was brought up is not the only way  things operate in life.  Other ways of doing things may be just as valid or maybe even more so than the way I was taught as a child. <br>
Different isn't necessarily wrong.
<p><code>--   (Class Lass) </code><p>


